    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix CRC computation error in NAS message integrity checking\n\n### Summary\nThe NAS message integrity checking logic was incorrectly forcing MAC matching for all messages when there was no security context, causing false positive CRC errors. Additionally, AUTHENTICATION REJECT messages and other EMM messages that can be sent without integrity protection were being rejected when they should be processed normally.\n\nThis fix removes the problematic MAC forcing logic and properly handles messages with SECURITY_HEADER_TYPE_NOT_PROTECTED according to 3GPP TS 24.301 specification.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/API/NETWORK/nas_message.c`: \n  - Removed the `NAS_CODE_TO_BE_MODIFIED` section that was forcing MAC values\n  - Added proper logic to skip integrity checking for messages with `SECURITY_HEADER_TYPE_NOT_PROTECTED`\n  - Added null check for emm_security_context in nas_message_decrypt\n  - Added necessary header includes for security header type constants\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Send an AUTHENTICATION REJECT message with security header type 0 (not protected)\n2. The message would be rejected due to failed integrity check even though it's valid according to 3GPP spec\n3. Alternatively, messages with mismatched MAC values would incorrectly pass integrity checking due to the forced MAC logic\n\nThe fix ensures that messages allowed to be sent without integrity protection are processed correctly, while still maintaining proper integrity checking for protected messages.\n"
}